the louie barozzi scholarship recognizes san jose state university international students and u.s. students participating in an sjsu certified study abroad program for their contributions to the community and commitment to international education and exchange.three awards are given annually: to an international undergraduate student, an international graduate student, and a study abroad and away participant.the application period is from february 1 to march 26, 2023.*note: international students should apply for the "louie barozzi--study abroad" scholarship you have studied abroad in another country (not in the u.s.) through a certified sjsu program. reviewers for the barozzi international student scholarship do not see applications for the barozzi study abroad scholarship. be sure you are applying for the correct scholarship. san jose state university, one washington square, san jose, ca 95192408-924-1000